 Sweezy]], [[Southern Arapaho]] (1881–1953) * [[Moses Stranger Horse]], [[Brulé|Brulé Lakota]] (1890–1941) * [[Quincy Tahoma]] aka "Water's Edge", [[Navajo people|Navajo]] (1920–1956)<ref>[http://www.askart.com/askart/artist.aspx?artist=70702 AskArt]</ref> * [[Jerome Tiger]] ([[Kocha]]), [[Muscogee Creek]]-[[Seminole]] * [[Johnny Tiger, Jr.]], [[Muscogee Creek]]-[[Seminole]] (1940–2015) * [[Jackie Traverse]], [[Anishinaabe]] (1969) * [[Monroe Tsatoke]], [[Kiowa]], one of the [[Kiowa Six]] * [[Awa Tsireh]] (Alfonso Roybal), [[San Ildefonso Pueblo]] (1898–1955) * [[Frank_Tuttle_(artist)|Frank Tuttle]], [[Yuki people|Yuki]], [[Wailaki]] and [[Maidu|Concow Maidu]] (1951) * [[Pablita Velarde]] ([[Tse Tsan]]), [[Santa Clara Pueblo]] (1918–2006) * [[Kay WalkingStick]], [[Cherokee Nation]]-[[Winnebago Tribe of Nebraska|Winnebago]] * [[Pop Wea|Pop Wea (Lori Tanner)]], [[Taos Pueblo]] (died 1966)<ref>Lester, p. 443</ref> * [[Dick West]] ([[Wah-pah-nah-yah]]), [[Cheyenne-Arapaho]] (1912–1996) * [[White Horse (chief)|White Horse]] ([[Tsen-tainte]]), [[Kiowa]] (died 1892) * [[Dyani White Hawk]], [[Sicangu Lakota]] (born 1976) * [[Emmi Whitehorse]], [[Navajo people|Navajo]] * [[Elizabeth Woody]], [[Navajo people|Navajo]]-[[Tenino people|Tenino (Warm Springs)]]-[[Wasco-Wishram|Wasco]]-[[Yakama]] (born 1959) * [[Melanie Yazzie]], [[Navajo people|Navajo]] {{div col end}}
